- Install Svelte Query using npm: `npm install @tanstack/svelte-query`
- Visit TanStack Query documentation at [tanstack.com](https://tanstack.com)
- Key configuration options include:
  - `queryKey`: Unique identifier for the query.
  - `queryFn`: Function that fetches data.
  - `initialData`: Initial data to display while fetching.
  - `staleTime`: Time in milliseconds after which data is considered stale.
  - `refetchInterval`: Interval at which data should be refetched.
- Use `useQuery` hook for managing queries:
  ```javascript
  import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/svelte-query';

  const fetchPosts = async () => {
    const response = await fetch('https://api.example.com/posts');
    return response.json();
  };

  const { data, isLoading, isError } = useQuery(['posts'], fetchPosts);
  ```
- For infinite loading, use `useInfiniteQuery`:
  ```javascript
  import { useInfiniteQuery } from '@tanstack/svelte-query';

  const fetchPosts = async ({ pageParam = 1 }) => {
    const response = await fetch(`https://api.example.com/posts?page=${pageParam}`);
    return response.json();
  };

  const { data, isLoading, isError, fetchNextPage } = useInfiniteQuery(['posts'], fetchPosts);
  ```
- For mutations, use `useMutation`:
  ```javascript
  import { useMutation } from '@tanstack/svelte-query';

  const createPost = async (newPost) => {
    const response = await fetch('https://api.example.com/posts', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify(newPost),
    });
    return response.json();
  };

  const mutation = useMutation(createPost, {
    onSuccess: (newData) => {
      // Handle successful creation
    },
    onError: (error) => {
      // Handle error
    },
  });

  mutation.mutate({ title: 'New Post', content: 'This is a new post.' });
  ```
- Latest version can be found on [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@tanstack/svelte-query).
